    • Class org.apache.plc4x.java.ads.api.commands.types.AdsStampHeader extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • timeStamp

          TimeStamp timeStamp
          8 bytes The timestamp is coded after the Windows FILETIME format. I.e. the value contains the number of the nano seconds, which passed since 1.1.1601. In addition, the local time change is not considered. Thus the time stamp is present as universal Coordinated time (UTC).

        • samples

          Samples samples
          4 bytes Number of elements of type AdsNotificationSample.

        • adsNotificationSamples

          List<E> adsNotificationSamples
          n bytes Array with elements of type AdsNotificationSample.

        • targetAmsNetId

          AmsNetId targetAmsNetId

        • targetAmsPort

          AmsPort targetAmsPort
          This is the AmsPort of the station, for which the packet is intended.

        • sourceAmsNetId

          AmsNetId sourceAmsNetId
          This contains the AmsNetId of the station, from which the packet was sent.

        • sourceAmsPort

          AmsPort sourceAmsPort
          This contains the AmsPort of the station, from which the packet was sent.

        • commandId

          Command commandId
          2 bytes.

        • stateFlags

          State stateFlags
          2 bytes.

        • dataLength

          DataLength dataLength
          4 bytes Size of the data range. The unit is byte.

        • code

          AmsError code
          4 bytes AMS error number. See ADS Return Codes.

        • invokeId

          Invoke invokeId
          4 bytes Free usable 32 bit array. Usually this array serves to send an Id. This Id makes is possible to assign a received response to a request, which was sent before.

  • Package org.apache.plc4x.java.ads.api.serial

    • Class org.apache.plc4x.java.ads.api.serial.AmsSerialAcknowledgeFrame extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • magicCookie

          MagicCookie magicCookie
          Id for detecting an AMS serial frame.

        • transmitterAddress

          TransmitterAddress transmitterAddress
          Address of the sending participant. This value can always be set to 0 for an RS232 communication, since it is a 1 to 1 connection and hence the participants are unique.

        • receiverAddress

          ReceiverAddress receiverAddress
          Receiver’s address. This value can always be set to 0 for an RS232 communication, since it is a 1 to 1 connection and hence the participants are unique.

        • fragmentNumber

          FragmentNumber fragmentNumber
          Number of the frame sent. Once the number 255 has been sent, it starts again from 0. The receiver checks this number with an internal counter.

        • userDataLength

          UserDataLength userDataLength
          The max. length of the AMS packet to be sent is 255. If larger AMS packets are to be sent then they have to be fragmented (not published at the moment).

        • crc

          CRC crc
